      <text class="text-lg">
        Bienvenue sur ma page ! :)
        <br><br>
        Currently a second-year PhD student, my research focuses on <b>probability applied to population biology</b>.
        <br>
        I am particularly interested in <b>interacting particle systems</b> and deriving scaling limits of <b>random trees and graphs</b> arising from these systems (genealogies, infection graphs in epidemiology, etc.)
        <br><br>
        I am co-supervised by <a class="link-secondary" href="https://homepage.univie.ac.at/emmanuel.schertzer/" target="_blank"><b>Emmanuel Schertzer</b></a> (University of Vienna, Austria), <a class="link-secondary" href="https://smile.cnrs.fr/people/amaury/" target="_blank"><b>Amaury Lambert</b></a> (ENS, Collège de France) and <a class="link-secondary" href="https://duchamps.perso.math.cnrs.fr/" target="_blank"><b>Jean-Jil Duchamps</b></a> (University of Franche-Comté).
        <br>
        I am part of the <a class="link-secondary" href="https://smile.cnrs.fr/" target="_blank"><b>SMILE</b></a> team hosted at Collège de France, Paris. I am also a member of the <a class="link-secondary" href="https://probabio-lmb.pages.math.cnrs.fr/" target="_blank"><b>Stochastic Modeling in Ecology & Evolution</b></a> group hosted at LMB, University of Franche-Comté and of the  <a class="link-secondary" href="https://sites.google.com/view/probabilityinvienna/home" target="_blank"><b>Probability in Vienna</b></a> community.
        


